研究方向 / Research Directions


					自然語言處理實驗室主要的研究方向是人類語言技術、資訊檢索與擷取、和網路探勘。我們研究人類語言知識的呈現、取得、運用和整合，以及異質資源多語資料的分類、檢索、過濾、擷取、和摘要。目前正研究的課題包括：


巨量資料 
知識圖譜 
網路意見探勘 
使用者意圖與行動之分析和預測
機器翻譯
自動摘要和問答
相關性、多樣性和新穎性資訊之分析、偵測和追蹤
社會媒體檢索
情境導向資訊檢索
跨語言跨媒體資訊檢索

學習式排序法在資訊檢索上的應用

新生招募

                    The major research directions of Natural Language Processing Laboratory are human language technologies, information retrieval and extraction, and web mining. We aim to studies (1) representation, acquisition, employment, and integration of human language knowledge, and (2) classification, retrieval, filtering, extraction, and summarization of multilingual data from heterogeneous resources, in particular, on the World Wide Web. Several research topics are under investigation: 


Big Data
Knowledge Graph
Web Opinion Mining
User Intent/Activity Analysis and Prediction
Machine Translation
Summarization, Question and Answering
Relevancy, Diversity, and Novelty Analysis, Detection and Tracking
Social Media Retrieval
Context-Aware Information Retrieval 
Cross-Language Cross-Media Retrieval 
Learning to Rank for Information Access

